metadata.name: CA Panico #87
metadata.description:
Third chapter of the trilogy dedicated to Stephen Wolfram's cellular automata.
 
Compared to CA Vista and CA Monti, CA Panico aims to further abstract the concept of landscape using CA rules in a more massive way.

The great variety of CA rules that controls the coloring and textures, noise influence, division into quadrants, chance of having glitches and outages all combined with 25 palettes and 5 different formats means that the outputs will be very varied and peculiar.

Press 'S' to download, you can zoom downloaded output to enjoy all the details.

metadata.name: Street Light #8
Try/Hatch #5
metadata.description:
In full screen view, click on the graphic to download plottable SVG in A3 format.

The color palette used in here is supposed to represent 25 Stabilo Point fineliners. The color values don't come from any official specification, though.

Every minted edition consists of 3 color layers:

- black-ish (pen number 46) with constant hatching distance
- two color layers with randomly chosen color and distance values

If you have a pen plotter, you can jump straight into making a physical drawing. Please be aware, that physical plot might differ from the digital version due to the pen and paper color differences.

Each group ID consists of an index, a HEX color value, and a Stabilo Point pen color number. In Inkscape, just convert groups to layers, and you can start to plot (probably the best experience with AxiDraw A3 pen plotter).

If you don't own a plotter or you want a regular print, simply convert your SVG to raster format.

metadata.name: fx(word) #52
metadata.description:
"Word" is a single unit of language that has meaning and can be spoken or written.
You can make your favorite word or brief sentence into a work using no more than 10 characters of fx(params).
No matter what language you use or what it means, it's going to turn into a work of art.

--

To highlight the rarity of the params value you set, i have set only text to appear in the feature list.

--

This project is made in 100% pure code with p5js
By Thion, April 2023

metadata.name: fREEDOM PUNK #25
metadata.description:
Welcome to fREEDOM PUNK world.
This project is Image Composition Layers pngs.
Created with 128x128 px format.
There are 9 Layers in this project. (included transparent png files)
- Background > 130 different images
- Body > 12 different body colors.
- Eyes > 24 different eyes.
- Nose > 13 different noses.
- Mouth > 58 different mouths.
- Eyeglasses > 19 different eyeglasses. (chance of nothing is much higher)
- Hair > 133 different hair-styles and headwear.
- Cloth > 160 different clothes.
- Things (In front of the punk) > 60 different things. (chance of nothing is much higher)

So you can generate your unique fREEDOM PUNKs for sure, due to very high possibilities by the layers.

Enjoy and good luck!
